      "content": "Here's a draft of a rejection email that balances professionalism and kindness:\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI wanted to personally reach out to you regarding the senior developer position we discussed earlier. We were truly impressed with your technical skills and the effort you put into preparing for the final round. Unfortunately, after careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience with distributed systems aligns more closely with our current needs.\n\nPlease know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were genuinely impressed by your qualifications and potential. We appreciate the time you took to interview with us and the enthusiasm you showed for the role.\n\nI want to thank you again for your interest in joining our team, and I wish you the best of luck in your ongoing job search. If you have any questions or concerns, please don't hesitate to reach out.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\n\nThis email aims to convey a sense of appreciation for Marcus's qualifications and a genuine regret that we couldn't move forward with him. The tone is professional, yet kind and gracious.",
